{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":867,"text":"So, raise your hand\nif you've seen somebody in your city"},{"time":4563,"text":"standing on a corner,\nholding a sign like this."},{"time":10409,"text":"I think we all have."},{"time":11682,"text":"If you're being honest,"},{"time":12871,"text":"at least one time,\nhave you wondered if they mean it?"},{"time":16758,"text":"If we offered them a job,\nwould they really take it?"},{"time":19689,"text":"And what would that job mean\nto them in their lives?"},{"time":23243,"text":"Well, this is a story\nabout what happened in my city"},{"time":26068,"text":"when we decided to find out,"},{"time":28712,"text":"when we decided to think differently\nabout panhandling,"},{"time":32123,"text":"and lift people up\nthrough the dignity of work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36134,"text":"We call it, \"There's a Better Way.\""},{"time":38384,"text":"We call it There's a Better Way"},{"time":39901,"text":"because I believe there's a better way\nto get the money you need"},{"time":42963,"text":"than panhandling on the corner."},{"time":45260,"text":"I believe there's a better way\nto help your brothers and sisters in need"},{"time":49182,"text":"than handing a few dollars\nout the car window."},{"time":52474,"text":"We know there's dignity in work."},{"time":55110,"text":"We also know that people are much more\nlikely to invest in themselves"},{"time":58530,"text":"if they believe that their community\nis willing to invest in them first."},{"time":63484,"text":"And because we're all wired\nto be kind and compassionate,"},{"time":66811,"text":"it always feels good to hand\na couple of dollars to someone"},{"time":70340,"text":"that is in need."},{"time":72807,"text":"But if you talk to panhandlers,\nmany of them will tell you"},{"time":76258,"text":"that your few dollars don't necessarily\ngo towards feeding the body,"},{"time":81472,"text":"they go towards feeding an addiction."},{"time":84484,"text":"There's a better way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86589,"text":"My name is Richard Berry,"},{"time":87885,"text":"and I have one of the best\njobs in the world."},{"time":90276,"text":"I get to be the mayor\nof a great American city,"},{"time":92734,"text":"Albuquerque, New Mexico."},{"time":95946,"text":"I was at lunch on July 17, 2015,\nin my great American city,"},{"time":102173,"text":"and on my way back to city hall,"},{"time":104421,"text":"I saw this gentleman standing on a corner."},{"time":107076,"text":"As you can see, he's holding a sign,"},{"time":109056,"text":"and his sign says he wants a job."},{"time":111673,"text":"But if you look closer at the picture,"},{"time":113539,"text":"you'll see he's standing\nunderneath a blue sign,"},{"time":115802,"text":"and that sign says, if you need help,\nif you need food or shelter"},{"time":119938,"text":"or you'd like to donate,"},{"time":121219,"text":"please call 311,\nour community service number."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125473,"text":"So why is this guy standing\nunderneath my sign with his sign?"},{"time":131069,"text":"Well, we wondered\nif anybody would call that 311 sign,"},{"time":133658,"text":"and as it turns out, they did --"},{"time":135238,"text":"11,000 times people called."},{"time":136993,"text":"I put those up in about 30 intersections."},{"time":139081,"text":"And we did connect them\nwith food and shelter and services."},{"time":142479,"text":"But yet he's still standing under my sign"},{"time":144565,"text":"with a sign that says he wants a job."},{"time":148088,"text":"It's simple: he wants a job."},{"time":151315,"text":"So I decided to do\nsomething rare in government."},{"time":154319,"text":"I decided to make the solution simpler\nrather than more complicated."},{"time":158626,"text":"I went back to my office,\nI gathered my staff around"},{"time":161175,"text":"and I said, \"We're going\nto take this man at his word,"},{"time":163810,"text":"and others like him."},{"time":165019,"text":"The man says he wants a job,\nwe're going to give him a job,"},{"time":167820,"text":"and we're going to make our city\nan even better place in the meantime.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":172099,"text":"You see, Albuquerque is a beautiful place."},{"time":174332,"text":"We're a mile high,"},{"time":175627,"text":"the Sandia Mountains on the east,"},{"time":177757,"text":"the Rio Grande runs through\nthe center of the city;"},{"time":180321,"text":"we're the home of the Albuquerque\nInternational Balloon Fiesta."},{"time":183409,"text":"On a day like today,"},{"time":184597,"text":"you could literally ski this morning\nand golf this afternoon."},{"time":188031,"text":"But there's always something to do --"},{"time":189946,"text":"always weeds to pull, litter to pick up."},{"time":192805,"text":"If you're going to have an initiative\nlike this in your city,"},{"time":195765,"text":"you have to ask yourself two questions."},{"time":197684,"text":"First one is: Is there anything\nleft to do in your city?"},{"time":200378,"text":"And if the answer is no,"},{"time":201584,"text":"would you please give me\nyour mayor's phone number,"},{"time":204016,"text":"because I need some advice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205363,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":206394,"text":"But the second question\nyou have to ask is this:"},{"time":208685,"text":"Are your solutions to panhandling working?"},{"time":212686,"text":"If you're like Albuquerque,"},{"time":213996,"text":"and you're taking the punitive\napproach like we used to,"},{"time":216666,"text":"handing out tickets to panhandlers\nor those who give them money,"},{"time":219824,"text":"I'm going to suggest\nthat your solutions aren't working,"},{"time":222522,"text":"and I know you're not getting\nto the root of your problem in your city."},{"time":226785,"text":"So if you have something to do"},{"time":229185,"text":"and you need people\nthat need something to do,"},{"time":231810,"text":"there's a better way."},{"time":233044,"text":"And the good news is,\nit's not that complicated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235860,"text":"This a 2006 Dodge van."},{"time":238674,"text":"It was in my motor pool\nnot doing anything."},{"time":241350,"text":"We put some new tires on it,\nwrapped it with a logo."},{"time":244316,"text":"This van now goes out to street corners\nwhere our panhandlers are --"},{"time":248135,"text":"we go to them."},{"time":249856,"text":"We stop the van, we get out,"},{"time":251326,"text":"we ask them if they\nwould like a day's work"},{"time":253382,"text":"rather than panhandling for the day."},{"time":256341,"text":"And if you wondered\nif they really mean it --"},{"time":259935,"text":"it takes us about an hour\nto fill this van up in the morning,"},{"time":262916,"text":"because almost everybody we ask\ntakes a job for the day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267373,"text":"But you need more than just a van."},{"time":269587,"text":"You need a super-fantastic\nhuman being to drive that van."},{"time":273276,"text":"And my super-fantastic human being,\nhis name is Will."},{"time":275970,"text":"This is him in the yellow vest."},{"time":277765,"text":"Will works at our local nonprofit partner."},{"time":280323,"text":"He works with the homeless every day."},{"time":282170,"text":"The panhandlers trust him,"},{"time":284696,"text":"he believes in them,"},{"time":286703,"text":"he hustles."},{"time":288285,"text":"I like to say, \"Where\nthere's a Will, there's a way.\""},{"time":291326,"text":"So if you're going to do\nthe Better Way campaign in your city,"},{"time":294344,"text":"you need to find yourself a Will,"},{"time":297340,"text":"because he's really one of the keys\nto making this successful"},{"time":301021,"text":"in the city of Albuquerque."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302645,"text":"You also need a great nonprofit partner."},{"time":304856,"text":"Ours is St. Martin's Hospitality Center."},{"time":307403,"text":"They've been in our community\nfor over 30 years."},{"time":309936,"text":"They provide counseling, food, shelter,"},{"time":312473,"text":"and if they don't provide it,"},{"time":313900,"text":"they know somebody in our city that does."},{"time":316550,"text":"But they do something much more\nfor me as the mayor."},{"time":319017,"text":"They provide agility."},{"time":320676,"text":"You see, it takes me two weeks,"},{"time":322913,"text":"maybe two months sometimes,"},{"time":324707,"text":"to onboard an employee\nwith the city of Albuquerque."},{"time":328024,"text":"So you could imagine --"},{"time":329803,"text":"my old Dodge van,"},{"time":330996,"text":"my super-fantastic human being, Will,"},{"time":333330,"text":"a great local nonprofit partner --"},{"time":335249,"text":"they drive to the corner,\nthere's a panhandler,"},{"time":337507,"text":"they say, \"Would you like\nto work for the day?\""},{"time":339785,"text":"The panhandler says, \"Yes,\""},{"time":341105,"text":"and Will says, \"Great! I'll be back\nin six weeks to pick you up.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":344277,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":345324,"text":"It wouldn't work."},{"time":346499,"text":"It's really important that we have\nthat agility in our program."},{"time":350762,"text":"And they do the paperwork,"},{"time":352460,"text":"they do the insurance,"},{"time":354008,"text":"they do all of the other forms\nthat I can't do quickly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":357790,"text":"We pay our panhandlers\nnine dollars an hour."},{"time":360345,"text":"We feed them once at the jobsite."},{"time":362250,"text":"At the end of the day,"},{"time":363427,"text":"our old Dodge van takes them\nright back to St. Martin's,"},{"time":366103,"text":"and they get connected\nwith counseling services."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369783,"text":"So far,"},{"time":370989,"text":"with the pilot program\nand a couple days a week,"},{"time":373495,"text":"and a fantastic human being\nand a Dodge van,"},{"time":376182,"text":"we've cleaned up 400 city blocks\nin the city of Albuquerque."},{"time":379602,"text":"We've picked up over 117,000 pounds\nof trash, weeds and litter."},{"time":384109,"text":"I don't know if you've ever\nweighed a tumbleweed,"},{"time":386456,"text":"but they don't weigh much,"},{"time":387761,"text":"so you can imagine the volume\nof material that we've picked up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391589,"text":"My city has 6,000 employees,"},{"time":395341,"text":"and none better\nthan my solid waste department."},{"time":398389,"text":"We send our trucks out\nat the end of the day,"},{"time":400561,"text":"they help the panhandlers\nput into the truck"},{"time":402817,"text":"the material they've picked up\nduring the day,"},{"time":405084,"text":"and we take it to the landfill."},{"time":406611,"text":"I'm lucky that I have city employees"},{"time":408399,"text":"that are willing to work side by side\nwith our panhandlers."},{"time":411364,"text":"They're lifting up our city\nwhile lifting up their lives."},{"time":414374,"text":"And like anything else --\nlisten, it takes resources."},{"time":417464,"text":"But the good news is it doesn't take much."},{"time":421181,"text":"We started with an old van,"},{"time":423044,"text":"a super-fantastic human being,"},{"time":424806,"text":"a great local nonprofit"},{"time":426124,"text":"and $50,000."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428648,"text":"But we also had to have community trust."},{"time":430838,"text":"And fortunately, we had built\nthat up in years prior to Better Way."},{"time":434958,"text":"We have a program called\n\"Albuquerque Heading Home,\""},{"time":437492,"text":"a Housing First model where we house\nthe chronically homeless,"},{"time":440560,"text":"and when I told my community\nwe wanted to do that differently,"},{"time":443669,"text":"I said there's a smart way\nto do the right thing."},{"time":446796,"text":"We have now housed 650 chronically\nhomeless, medically vulnerable --"},{"time":450909,"text":"frankly, most likely to die\non the streets in our city."},{"time":454357,"text":"We commissioned our university,\nthey studied it."},{"time":456750,"text":"We could tell the taxpayers,\nwe can save you 31.6 percent"},{"time":460428,"text":"over the cost of leaving someone\nto struggle for survival on the streets."},{"time":464430,"text":"We've now saved over five million dollars\nwhile housing 650 people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":468452,"text":"So we had that community trust,"},{"time":470443,"text":"but we had to have a little bit more\nof an honest conversation also"},{"time":473682,"text":"as a community,"},{"time":475193,"text":"because we had to get people to understand"},{"time":477243,"text":"that when they hand\nthose five dollars out the window,"},{"time":479810,"text":"they might actually be minimizing\ntheir opportunity"},{"time":482230,"text":"to help the person in need,\nand here's why:"},{"time":484310,"text":"that five dollars might go\nto buying some fast food today --"},{"time":488147,"text":"a lot of times it goes to buying\ndrugs and alcohol."},{"time":491172,"text":"That same five dollars,"},{"time":492347,"text":"if you gave it to one of our shelters,"},{"time":494629,"text":"could feed seven people today."},{"time":496414,"text":"And if you gave it to one of our local\nfood banks or food pantries,"},{"time":500720,"text":"we could actually feed\n20 people with that money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":505891,"text":"People ask,\"Well, Albuquerque\nis 600,000 people -- million, metro --"},{"time":510763,"text":"this wouldn't work in our city,\nwe're too big, we're too small.\""},{"time":513878,"text":"I disagree; if you have\none panhandler on one city block,"},{"time":516597,"text":"you can do this."},{"time":517777,"text":"If you live in a city\nof eight-and-half million people,"},{"time":520419,"text":"you can do this."},{"time":521598,"text":"It doesn't matter what you do."},{"time":523099,"text":"It's not the work that you do,\nit's the dignity of the work."},{"time":525985,"text":"You could do anything."},{"time":527167,"text":"So I think any city could do this."},{"time":529291,"text":"And people say to me,"},{"time":530514,"text":"\"Mayor, that's just a little too simple."},{"time":533377,"text":"It can't work that way.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":535485,"text":"But I tell you what, friends:"},{"time":537058,"text":"when you go to a street corner"},{"time":538525,"text":"and you engage with a panhandler\nwith dignity and respect,"},{"time":541477,"text":"maybe for the first time in years,\nmaybe in their life,"},{"time":544201,"text":"and you tell them that you believe in them"},{"time":546280,"text":"and that this is their city\nas much as it's your city,"},{"time":548976,"text":"and that you actually need their help\nto make our place better,"},{"time":553767,"text":"and you understand that this\nisn't the answer to all their problems,"},{"time":557109,"text":"but at least it's a start,"},{"time":559051,"text":"an amazing thing happens."},{"time":561253,"text":"When they get out on the jobsite\nand they start working together,"},{"time":564623,"text":"you start seeing amazing things happen."},{"time":566544,"text":"They see teamwork; they see\nthe fact that they can make a difference."},{"time":569871,"text":"And at the end of the day,"},{"time":571136,"text":"when they get back to St. Martin's\nin that old Dodge van,"},{"time":573856,"text":"they're much more likely to sign up\nfor whatever services they need --"},{"time":577208,"text":"substance abuse, mental health\ncounseling, you name it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579951,"text":"So far with our pilot program,"},{"time":582395,"text":"we've offered\nabout 1,700 days of day work."},{"time":585288,"text":"We've connected 216 people\nto permanent employment opportunities."},{"time":589867,"text":"Twenty people actually qualified\nfor our Housing First model,"},{"time":593562,"text":"Heading Home,"},{"time":594764,"text":"and they've been housed."},{"time":595947,"text":"And over 150 people have been connected"},{"time":598130,"text":"to mental health substance abuse services"},{"time":600972,"text":"through There's a Better Way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":602692,"text":"This is me just two weeks ago,"},{"time":606938,"text":"at St. Martin's,"},{"time":608130,"text":"doing our point-in-time survey"},{"time":609606,"text":"that we do every two years."},{"time":611549,"text":"I'm interviewing a gentleman\nwho's homeless, like we do,"},{"time":614986,"text":"getting his information,\nfiguring out where he's from,"},{"time":617754,"text":"how he got there,"},{"time":619506,"text":"what we can do to help him."},{"time":621133,"text":"And you notice he's holding the same sign\nthat the guy was holding in 2015,"},{"time":625128,"text":"same sign I walked out with here today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628167,"text":"So you have to ask yourself:\nIs it really making a difference?"},{"time":631163,"text":"Absolutely it's making a difference."},{"time":633196,"text":"Albuquerque is now\none of the national leaders"},{"time":635878,"text":"in combating some of the most stubborn\nand persistent social issues"},{"time":639128,"text":"that we have."},{"time":640303,"text":"Combined with Albuquerque Heading Home,"},{"time":642206,"text":"the Better Way program,"},{"time":643421,"text":"Albuquerque has reduced unsheltered\nhomelessness in our city"},{"time":646385,"text":"by 80 percent last year."},{"time":649403,"text":"Since I took over as mayor,"},{"time":650741,"text":"we've been able to reduce the chronic\nhomeless population in our city"},{"time":654029,"text":"by 40 percent."},{"time":656130,"text":"And by HUD's definition,"},{"time":657469,"text":"we've gotten to functional zero,"},{"time":659186,"text":"which means we've literally ended\nveteran homelessness"},{"time":661858,"text":"in the city of Albuquerque,"},{"time":663222,"text":"by being intentional."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664676,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":670957,"text":"So I'm happy to report\nthat other cities are hearing about this,"},{"time":674192,"text":"other mayors are calling us --"},{"time":675760,"text":"Chicago, Seattle, Denver, Dallas --"},{"time":678507,"text":"and are now starting to implement programs"},{"time":681067,"text":"where they bring the dignity\nof work to the equation."},{"time":684166,"text":"And I can't wait to learn from them."},{"time":686045,"text":"I can't wait to see\nwhat their experiment looks like,"},{"time":688746,"text":"what their pilot project looks like,"},{"time":690805,"text":"so we can start taking\na collective approach nationally"},{"time":693402,"text":"through the dignity of work."},{"time":694802,"text":"And I want to commend them --"},{"time":696207,"text":"the mayors, their communities,\ntheir nonprofits --"},{"time":698642,"text":"for the work that they're doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":700854,"text":"So who's next?"},{"time":703493,"text":"Are you and your city ready to step up?"},{"time":706770,"text":"Are you ready to think differently\nabout these persistent social issues?"},{"time":710960,"text":"Are you ready to lift people up\nin your community"},{"time":713300,"text":"through the dignity of work,"},{"time":715253,"text":"and make your city\nprofoundly better in many ways?"},{"time":719211,"text":"Well, if you are, my friends,\nI promise you there is a better way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":722533,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":723715,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}